@proux01 thanks for your contribution, it's likely all of this will be integrated. I will come back to your PR later to help with the tidying. Just some general remarks about mathcomp style meanwhile:
- do not use `{}` to focus, use the [mathcomp conventions](https://github.com/math-comp/math-comp/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#indentation-in-proof-scripts) about indentation and terminators instead.
- do not name hypothesis `Hsomething`, as expained [here](https://github.com/math-comp/math-comp/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#naming-of-variables), give meaningful names based on their scope (the longer the scope the more meaningful the name).

